msgctxt "talk00"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Welcome to <2.se_co>Dueling Peaks Stable<3.re_co>!\n"
"What do you think of the place?\n"
"Pretty nice, yeah?\n"
"<4.so>It might be hard to imagine now, but this\n"
"place was nearly destroyed about 100\n"
"years ago.\n"
"<5.so>However, thanks to the blessings of the\n"
"<6.se_co>Dueling Peaks<7.re_co>, everything is full of life\n"
"again.\n"
"Even the wild horses are back. There's a\n"
"lot of energy in this place!\n"
"\n"
"<8.so>So where are you heading? Both\n"
"Kakariko Village and Hateno Village\n"
"are nearby.<9.ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: sound
msgctxt "talk03"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Huh? Did you not see any horses on\n"
"your way here?\n"
"\n"
"Certainly not as many as in years past,\n"
"but there are still quite a few around...\n"
"\n"
"<2.so>Horses in the wild are...well, wild!\n"
"No one has trained or cared for them.\n"
"\n"
"If you manage to catch one, let my\n"
"brother Tasseren know. He'll register the\n"
"horse for you! \n"
"My boys are wellsprings of information\n"
"about horses, so feel free to pick\n"
"their brains."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: sound
#. 3: sound
msgctxt "talk04"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Kakariko Village is the village where the\n"
"Sheikah clan lives.\n"
"\n"
"<2.so>It's said that, some time ago, they had\n"
"advanced techniques that were more\n"
"powerful than anything anyone had seen.\n"
"But that power put them at odds with the\n"
"king at the time, and they were scattered\n"
"across the land...\n"
"<3.so>Anyway, if you leave here and follow the\n"
"road straight to the north, you'll find a\n"
"big bridge.\n"
"Cross that and keep following the path,\n"
"and you'll come to the Kakariko Village\n"
"gate."
msgstr ""

